What people are saying... 







AP Technical Search has served the technical placement needs of Cameron Compression Systems for many years. I would highly recommend the services of Ron Papaj and his staff because of their ability to identify strong candidates who have well-documented backgrounds that we would otherwise have difficulty finding. AP Technical Search is friendly, courteous, and demonstrates a level of professionalism that Cameron demands from today’s search firm.
–Scott Boyko, Six Sigma Business Leader, Cameron Compression Systems






I’ve had the pleasure to work with AP. Professionals for 3 years now. After earning a Master’s degree at RIT in May ’07, I spent the summer months just like any other recent graduate: submitting online applications, suiting up for interviews, and distributing my resume to various recruiting agencies. Nothing was working. In the fall, I was introduced to AP Professionals by a close friend and the difference was remarkable. In just a few short months, I was hired as a web developer at one of the Top 10 advertising and marketing agencies in WNY. AP didn’t just get me a job, they found me a career and put me on a path to success. Now as an IT Director, I don’t hesitate to call AP when I have a position to fill. Their personal attention to their clients and their dedication to find the perfect fit for both parties is truly second-to-none in the Buffalo market.
–Ryan DiMillo, IT Director, Quinlan & Co. 






I can’t say enough about what a great job Kelly and her team have done for us. Not only is everyone at AP an absolute pleasure to work with, they make every effort to make the process as stress free as possible and have been so accommodating in every situation. I am always confident that AP sends me only the best candidates and every one I have met with has been professional and capable. Even when the orders are big, I’m never worried that it’s something they can’t handle! Kelly and her team members go above and beyond for me! Even with how busy I know they are, they make me feel like I am their only client!
—Lynette E. Myers, Talent Management of Independent Health






Searching for a new job especially in tough times can be difficult and stressful. I was fortunate enough to get in contact with AP (Matt Taylor) early on in my search. From the beginning they made it a point to get to know me professionally and personally and made sure they understood where I wanted to go with my career and what type of positions I would want. Unlike other recruiters I had been working with, AP only presented opportunities that had the potential to be the right fit for me instead of forcing me into interviews that I was unqualified for or uninterested in. They were always upfront with me willing to answer any questions even if it was well after business hours. I always felt comfortable talking through other opportunities with them because I knew they were concerned for finding the right fit for me. As a result I am now at a successful company with great opportunity for growth and advancement. I continue to recommend AP to family and friends confident they will have the same positive experience that I had.
—Ben Roushey, Controller, Power Management






For me, AP Professionals ranks as the #1 placement agency in the Rochester area. I was introduced to a team of specialists who were professional, educated, helpful and a pleasure to work with. Having to unexpectedly find a job can be an emotional and trying experience. The staff at AP Professionals eased my concerns and functioned as an experienced team to quickly secure me employment. I would highly recommend them. Should I need to seek employment again in my career, they will be my first phone call.
—Roxann Gendron, Controller, Conifer Realty









